Japan May Raise Sales Tax to 8% in October 2013, Yomiuri Says

-- B y   T a k e h i k o   K u m a k u r a
-- 
2011-10-23T21:45:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-23/japan-may-raise-sales-tax-to-8-in-october-2013-yomiuri-says.html
The Japanese government will propose
that the sales tax be raised to as high as 8 percent in October
2013 and 10 percent in fiscal 2015, the Yomiuri newspaper said.  The government may submit legislation next year, the
newspaper reported, without saying where it obtained the
information.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Takehiko Kumakura at 
 tkumakura@bloomberg.net  